Matthew Van Meter::Friday, February 26, 2016 5:05 AM::<comment>Hey thanks for the compliment. That means a lot.To answer your question: no, Booker does not apply to state courts. There's one simple reason for this: the Sentencing Reform Act also didn't apply to state courts. A few states have guideline-like policies (indeed, the SRA was based on state initiatives), but they vary as much as anything does state-by-state.If you're interested in the nitty-gritty, here's a link to the National Center for State Courts booklet on guidelines. It's not worth reading in detail, but the overview is pretty good. http://www.ncsc.org/~/media/Mi...</comment>

